most serious poem in the three books. I'm trying to remember, was this when he
was recalling his dead friend who was buried up on the hill? No, it's after

06:08.280 --> 06:26.480
that. and Tristal and Tor are logging for the winter, and Stell goes to visit
them. And Tristal sings in this song, and Stell is touched by it. And later on,

